      "question": "The following table shows the daily pocket allowance of $50$ children in a locality. Find the mean daily pocket allowance using the direct method.\n\n| Daily allowance (in $\u20b9$) | $100-120$ | $120-140$ | $140-160$ | $160-180$ | $180-200$ |\n| :--- | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: |\n| Number of children | $12$ | $14$ | $8$ | $6$ | $10$ |",
      "answer": "$\u20b9 145.20$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Find the class mark ($x_i$) for each interval using the formula $x_i = \\frac{\\text{upper limit} + \\text{lower limit}}{2}$.",
          "Multiply each frequency ($f_i$) by its corresponding class mark ($x_i$) to get $f_ix_i$.",
          "Calculate the sum of all frequencies $\\sum f_i$ and the sum of all products $\\sum f_ix_i$.",
          "Apply the direct mean formula $\\bar{x} = \\frac{\\sum f_ix_i}{\\sum f_i}$ to find the final result."
        ],
        "derivation": "$x_1 = \\frac{100+120}{2} = 110, x_2 = 130, x_3 = 150, x_4 = 170, x_5 = 190 \\\\ \\sum f_i = 12 + 14 + 8 + 6 + 10 = 50 \\\\ \\sum f_ix_i = (12 \\times 110) + (14 \\times 130) + (8 \\times 150) + (6 \\times 170) + (10 \\times 190) \\\\ \\sum f_ix_i = 1320 + 1820 + 1200 + 1020 + 1900 = 7260 \\\\ \\text{Mean} = \\frac{7260}{50} = 145.2$"
      },
